'''Av√©''', ('''vierbe''' / ''verb'' / ''verbo''): *to have *avere
== Usage Note == This verb is the most commonly used auxilliary (along with [[Molisan/verbs/√®sse|√®sse]]). It is not directly synonomous to the Italian verb ''avere'' in other cases. Rather, the verb [[Molisan/verbs/ten√©|ten√©]] is used. Av√© is never used as a main verb, it only exists as a "helping verb". It is often marked with a silent initial 'h' as in Italian. It is also an essential part of the verb [[Molisan/Verbs/Av√© da|av√© da]] (dovere, to need to).
